g.text: All operations were carried out under nitrogen by using conventional Schlenk techniques.
Solvents were dried by refluxing over sodium-benzophenone ketyl (THF, diethyl ether) or CaH
(pentane, dichloromethane) and were freshly distilled prior to use. The silica gel used for
chromatography (J. T. Baker, silica gel for flash chromatography) was nitrogen saturated. The
yields refer to analytically pure compounds and were not optimized.
